hr size=1> As of now this game is dominated in the RvR by the stealth classes.<br>
In fact, it is so dominated, that players w/o stealth or w/o counter-measures<br>
can only huddle together for protection, knowing that the stealthed player can get<br>
ONE but then they get killed in return. Running around solo is a invitation to be<br>
PK'ed<br>
<br>
The assualt phase is dominated by 'How long can we keep the archers mezzed'<br>
<br>
That is really how it is. If the archers have free reign to fire, the assault is over.<br>
<br>
The game really is sadly, how much money you can get the 'other' side to spend<br>
on 'doors'<br>
<br>
That is TRUELY what it comes down to.  The guild institutes dues to pay for the cost of doors.  The money pyramid expands to feed wood purchase.<br>
<br>
It is comical, in a way. This is NOT to say the game isnt fun, IT IS.<br>
<br>
However, to consider that your entire existance is condenced into your ability to<br>
buy and carry wood, kinda takes the drama away. <br>
<br>
Also, certain guilds can and do cheat. There are several programs out that allow<br>
TOTAL information. That removes the confusion and fog of war.<br>
You are as helpless as Iraqi tanks at night on a road.<br>
<br>
In one example, there is a planned assualt on a know 'cheating' guild keep.<br>
They are defeated (by numbers) and the keep is taken. New doors installed,<br>
as many upgrades as possible done.  So you log for the night.<br>
In the morning, you find that the keep was re-taken by the cheating guild<br>
one hour after you took it from them. I sure wish I could organize a counter<br>
attack that fast.<br>
<br>
If these flaws are ever addressed you may have a pretty good game here.<br>
<br>
Chiteng<br>
